Step 1: Identify the cash components from the balance sheet as of the end date.  
• Cash on Hand = 927447.32  
• Bank Deposits = 71662.08  

Step 2: Compute the total cash available.  
Total Cash = 927447.32 + 71662.08 = 999109.40  

Step 3: Identify the current liabilities (current debt) from the balance sheet as of the end date.  
• Accounts Payable = 3350120.00  
• Taxes Payable = 39599.66  
Total Current Liabilities = 3350120.00 + 39599.66 = 3389719.66  

Step 4: Calculate the Cash to Current Debt Ratio.  
Ratio = Total Cash / Total Current Liabilities = 999109.40 / 3389719.66 ≈ 0.2947  

Rounded to two decimals, the ratio is 0.29.

Thus, the final answer is:
